document_data.History:
In the early history of Ravens Bluff, the city's founders hired the [[Gondar]] priest [[Collun Rhodes]] to help plan the city's sewer systems.<ref>{{Cite polyhedron/135/City Stories: The Temple of Gond|10}}

Some time in the mid-14{{th}} century [[DR]], a great number of [[tanar'ri]] were discovered dwelling within the sewers after a [[baatezu]] hunter arrived to aid and direct local [[adventurer]]s to wipe them out.<ref>{{Cite trumpeter/2-4}}

Following his return to the position of mayor in late [[1371 DR]], [[Charles Oliver O'Kane]] worked with Lady [[Lauren DeVillars]] on expensive public works projects, which included the establishment of better sewers.<ref>{{Cite polyhedron/147/Pillars of Ravens Bluff|20}}

document_data.Notable Inhabitants:
* [[Chaney]], a [[doppelganger]] and Ravens Bluff's Chief Spy, had a lair in the sewers.<ref>{{Cite polyhedron/148/Pillars of Ravens Bluff|21}}
* [[Cudzu]].<ref>
* [[Jedderk Aldo]], an exterminator, was often found in the sewers dealing with vermin alongside his [[kobold]] assistants, [[Gartt]] and [[Snarr]]. Both of whom he had discovered one day living in the sewers beneath Ravens Bluff's business district.{{Cite polyhedron/83/The New Rogues Gallery: The Rat Catcher of Ravens Bluff}}
* [[Snuggly]], an information officer of the [[Silent Network]], could often be found in the sewers.<ref> His other job as a lead engineer made him in charge of sewer repairs.<ref>{{Cite polyhedron/141/The Silent Network|27}}
